        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3325854519" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11399336938122302371"><b>This book makes me want to give everyone I know a warm hug and a cup of tea. </b><br/>I&apos;m not really sure how to rate this one, but I do know that everyone should read it. As someone who has been diagnosed with anxiety and PTSD, this book means a lot to me, even if Matt Haig&apos;s journey with mental health has been very different from my own. You can get through it in a single sitting, but I&apos;d recommend savouring this one and taking time to think about Haig&apos;s words in relation to people you know.</span>
  <span id="freeText11399336938122302371" style="display:none"><b>This book makes me want to give everyone I know a warm hug and a cup of tea. </b><br />I'm not really sure how to rate this one, but I do know that everyone should read it. As someone who has been diagnosed with anxiety and PTSD, this book means a lot to me, even if Matt Haig's journey with mental health has been very different from my own. You can get through it in a single sitting, but I'd recommend savouring this one and taking time to think about Haig's words in relation to people you know.</span>
